    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n6422" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νέμεσις</span></b> , dat. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νεμέσσῑ</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">-ει</span>), (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νέμω</span>,
          ‘dispensation’): just <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">indignation, anger, censure;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">οὐ νέμεσις</span>, ‘no wonder,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 3.156</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ἐν φρεσὶ θέσθε αἰδῶ καὶ νέμεσιν</span>,
          self-respect and a ‘regard for men's indignant blame,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 13.122</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            6.351</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
